                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.6511/1338: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-03T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 3, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>144. Your 297, March 1, 1 p.m. The Department had taken into consideration the
                    points raised in your telegram under reference but considered that the continued
                    presence of German Consular Officers at Naples and Palermo in fact constituted a
                    violation of the most-favored-nation principle.</p>
                <p>On the other hand it may be preferable for the time being to omit Seattle from
                    the restrictive measures proposed. Consequently your request to the Foreign
                    Office should be limited to the closing of the offices at Detroit and
                    Newark.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
